jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154459/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-MTB-flat-pedal-mountain-bike-shoe-2021-5-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>The early season has meant limited chances to get out and try the Hellion Elite, so I took the chance to do some back to back testing with these and the Vice Mid at our asphalt pump tracks. The increase in grip the 4.0 Max rubber provides is instantly noticeable. You have to consciously want to move your foot around the pedal, otherwise, theyâ€™re firmly locked in place.</p><p>Compared to the Vice Mid, the Hellion Elite also offers a much firmer feel at the pedals. This should make the shoe much better for longer trail rides, but on the pump track, I preferred the feel of the Vice Mid.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/