s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-1127x420.jpg 1127w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex.jpg 2415w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-297x111.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-800x298.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-120x45.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-768x286.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-1536x572.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-2048x763.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-696x259.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-1068x398.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-1920x716.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/16154621/Ride-Concepts-Hellion-Elite-toe-flex-1127x420.jpg 1127w\"></a></p><p>Along those lines, the Hellion Elite seems like it will take quite a bit longer to break in compared to the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/04/ride-concepts-teams-up-with-andreu-lacondeguy-for-new-vice-mid-shoe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Vice Mid (which really needed no break-in at all)</a>. The thicker material around the toe caused some uncomfortable creasing right out of the box, but after a few laps it had already started to loosen up. I suspect that with a few more rides, the Hellion Elites would become much more comfortable.</p><p>For my needs, thereâ€™s no question that Iâ€™d reach for the Vice Mid over this shoe, but thatâ€™s really no surprise since I donâ€™t do longer trail and enduro rides in flats. For those that do, and that want the maximum grip out of their outsole, the Hellion Elite fits the bill.</p><p><a href=\"https://rideconcepts.com/pages/hellion-elite\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>rideconcepts.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"442f8238ec9f80aa2028127adf9d3825074323bd1cbf50c51880eee8fea14329","category":"Cycling"}